Adaro, Bumi Resources, Energi Mega: Indonesia Equity Preview

-- B y   F e m i   A d i
-- 
2011-07-18T02:04:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-18/adaro-bumi-resources-energi-mega-indonesia-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and share prices are as of the previous close.  The  Jakarta Composite index (JCI)  advanced 25.57 points, or 0.6
percent, to 4,023.20, a record close.  Coal producers: Power-station coal  prices  at  Australia ’s
Newcastle port, an Asian benchmark, dropped 1.5 percent to
$120.61 in the week ended July 15, according to the  globalCOAL
NEWC Index . PT Bumi Resources (BUMI IJ),  Asia ’s largest exporter
of power-station coal, was unchanged at 2,950 rupiah and PT
Adaro Energy (ADRO IJ), the second largest, advanced 2 percent
to 2,550 rupiah.  Oil companies : Crude oil futures gained 1.6 percent to
$97.24 a barrel in  New York  on July 15. Oil was at $97.22 in
after-hours trading today.  PT Medco Energi Internasional (MEDC IJ), Indonesia’s
biggest listed oil company, dropped 1.1 percent to 2,275 rupiah
and PT Energi Mega Persada (ENRG IJ), the second largest,
dropped 2.4 percent to 200 rupiah.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Femi Adi in Jakarta at 
